 250:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****     [..]
 251:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****     This subsection provides a set of functions allowing to initialize the USARTx or the UARTy
 252:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****     in asynchronous mode.
 253:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****       (+) For the asynchronous mode the parameters below can be configured:
 254:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) Baud Rate
 255:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) Word Length
 256:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) Stop Bit
 257:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) Parity: If the parity is enabled, then the MSB bit of the data written
 258:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****              in the data register is transmitted but is changed by the parity bit.
 259:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) Hardware flow control
 260:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) Receiver/transmitter modes
 261:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) Over Sampling Method
 262:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) One-Bit Sampling Method
 263:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****       (+) For the asynchronous mode, the following advanced features can be configured as well:
 264:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) TX and/or RX pin level inversion
 265:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) data logical level inversion
 266:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) RX and TX pins swap
 267:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) RX overrun detection disabling
 268:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) DMA disabling on RX error
 269:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) MSB first on communication line
 270:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****         (++) auto Baud rate detection
 271:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****     [..]
 272:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****     The HAL_UART_Init(), HAL_HalfDuplex_Init(), HAL_LIN_Init()and HAL_MultiProcessor_Init()API
 273:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****     follow respectively the UART asynchronous, UART Half duplex, UART LIN mode
 274:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****     and UART multiprocessor mode configuration procedures (details for the procedures
 275:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart.c ****     are available in reference manual).
